Hungary Mulls Foreclosure Moratorium Extension, Nemzet Reports

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-02-21T07:28:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/hungary-mulls-foreclosure-moratorium-extension-nemzet-reports.html
Hungary’s government is considering
extending a real estate foreclosure moratorium beyond April 15,
 Magyar Nemzet  reported, citing the Public Administration and
Justice Ministry.  The extended moratorium probably won’t apply to everyone
yet will “almost certainly” protect those with mortgages, the
daily newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  